#: content/docs/developing.md:6
msgid "Developing the shell"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:8
msgid "Plasma Bigscreen is developed as a [KDE project](https://kde.org), and thus uses KDE infrastructure for development and translations."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:10
msgid "Our **source code** is hosted on the [KDE Invent GitLab](https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-bigscreen)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:12
msgid "See detailed instructions on the [developer wiki](https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-bigscreen/-/wikis/Building-and-Testing-Locally) for building and testing the shell."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:14
msgid "To contribute **translations**, please see the [KDE Localization webpage](https://l10n.kde.org/) and join the team for your desired language."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:16
msgid "Developing new apps"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:18
msgid "We currently do not provide a first party general-purpose framework for building TV applications."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:20
msgid "However, this is Linux! You have the freedom to use frameworks that you are comfortable with to develop TV-focused applications. Some popular options include:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:21
msgid "[Qt](https://www.qt.io/development/qt-framework) + [Qt Quick](https://www.qt.io/product/qt6/qml-book)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:22
msgid "[Electron](https://www.electronjs.org/) or [Tauri](https://v2.tauri.app/) (Web-based apps)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:23
msgid "[Flutter](https://flutter.dev/)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:25
msgid "Things to keep in mind when developing apps for TVs:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:26
msgid "Support arrow navigation and Esc to \"go back\"."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:27
msgid "Only capture direct controller input when the window is focused."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:28
msgid "Users may have varied display scalings set, it can be useful to provide in-app scaling options."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/docs/developing.md:0
msgid "Developing"
